<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <!-- Download Raleway -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="//fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Raleway" />

    <!-- Responsive webpage -->
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">

    <!-- Download Bootstrap and dependencies -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.3.1/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-ggOyR0iXCbMQv3Xipma34MD+dH/1fQ784/j6cY/iJTQUOhcWr7x9JvoRxT2MZw1T" crossorigin="anonymous">

    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.3.1.slim.min.js" integrity="sha384-q8i/X+965DzO0rT7abK41JStQIAqVgRVzpbzo5smXKp4YfRvH+8abtTE1Pi6jizo" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/popper.js/1.14.7/umd/popper.min.js" integrity="sha384-UO2eT0CpHqdSJQ6hJty5KVphtPhzWj9WO1clHTMGa3JDZwrnQq4sF86dIHNDz0W1" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
    <script src="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.3.1/js/bootstrap.min.js" integrity="sha384-JjSmVgyd0p3pXB1rRibZUAYoIIy6OrQ6VrjIEaFf/nJGzIxFDsf4x0xIM+B07jRM" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</head>

<style>
    .partner {
        padding-top: 2%;
        font-family: "Raleway";
        text-align: center;
        letter-spacing: 3px;
        font-size: 150%;
        font-weight: 1000;
    }

    .logos {
        margin-top: -1%;
        text-align: center;
    }

    .title-box-container {
        text-align: center;
    }

    .title-box {
        display: inline-block;
    }

    .title {
        text-align: right;
        font-family: "Hey November";
        font-size: 600%;
    }

    .subtitle {
        margin-top: -1.5%;
        font-family: "Raleway";
        text-align: right;
        letter-spacing: 3px;
        font-size: 150%;
        font-weight: 1000;
    }

    .challenge-green {
        width: 100%; 
        height: 100%; 
        background-image: url(<%= image_path("challenge-green.png") %>);
        background-size: 100% 100%;
    }

    .first-title {
        font-family: "Raleway Black";
        font-size: 200%;
        font-weight: 100;
        color: white;
        letter-spacing: 4px;
        padding-left: 5%;
        padding-right: 30%;
    }

    .padded-above {
        padding-top: 25%;
    }

    .padded-above-orange {
        padding-top: 30%;
        margin-top: -15%;
    }

    .first-desc {
        font-family: "Raleway Semibold";
        padding-left: 5%;
        padding-right: 30%;
        text-align: justify;
        color: white;
    }

    .padded-below {
        padding-bottom: 25%;
    }

    .padded-below-orange {
        padding-bottom: 2%;
    }

    .challenge-orange {
        width: 100%; 
        height: 100%; 
        background-image: url(<%= image_path("challenge-orange.png") %>);
        background-size: 100% 100%;
    }

    .second-title {
        font-family: "Raleway Black";
        font-size: 200%;
        font-weight: 100;
        color: #F26648;
        letter-spacing: 4px;
        padding-right: 3%;
        padding-left: 25%;
        text-align: right;
    }

    .second-desc {
        font-family: "Raleway Semibold";
        padding-left: 25%;
        padding-right: 3%;
        text-align: justify;
        direction: rtl;
        color: #F26648;
    }

    .page-foot {
        background-color: #F26648;
        padding-top: 4px;
        padding-bottom: 4px;
        text-align: center;
    }

    .last-link {
        font-family: Raleway;
        font-weight: 900;
        letter-spacing: 4px;
        color: white;
        font-size: 200%;
    }
</style>

<body>
<div class="container">
    <h2 class="partner">PARTNERS:</h2>
    <div class="logos">
        <%= image_tag("logo-nusdvo.png", height: "66px") %> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;
        <%= image_tag("logo-welfare.png", height: "111px") %> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;
        <%= image_tag("logo-nusit.png") %>
    </div>

    <div class="title-box-container">
        <div class="title-box">
            <h1 class="title">CHALLENGE STATEMENTS</h1>
            <h2 class="subtitle">DARE TO INSPIRE</h2>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="challenge-green">
        <h1 class="first-title padded-above">#1 2020 NUSSU WELFARE DIARY</h1>
        <div class="first-desc">
            <p>The NUSSU Welfare Dairy is published annually by the NUSSU Welfare Committee and is distributed during the NUS Student Life Fair to the NUS population in the month of August. The journal design should include:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Cover: (Design to be embossed on it)</li>
                <ul>
                    <li>Name: NUSSU Welfare Diary</li>
                    <li>Year: (AY) 2020/2021</li>
                    <li>Dark colour(s) (eg. navy blue, dark brown, black) with accent colour of choice</li>
                </ul>
                <li>Front page: (this belongs to...)</li>
                <li>Monthly dividers: 1 page per month (Aug 2020 -Jul 2021), with jewel toned colour background of choice, and writings in block letters with font of choice. You may want to add in icons or symbols representative of the respective months to increase the visual appeal (eg. Christmas tree for December). An example would be:
                <div class="example-divider">
                </div>
                <br>
                Jewel tone colours are richly saturated hues named for gems including sapphire blue, ruby red, amethyst purple, citrine yellow, and emerald green. Here are some examples of jewel tones:
                <div class="example-jewel-tone">
                </div>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>
        <br>

        <h1 class="first-title">COMPANY BACKGROUND</h1>
        <div class="first-desc padded-below">
        <p>NUSSU Welfare is a committee that aims to enrich the welfare of NUS students through various events, such as Exam Welfare Pack, Free Cone Day, Welfare Diary, etc., to improve their social and psychological well-being.</p>
        </div>
        <%= button_to 'Read More',  static_pages_challenge_statement_1_path(@challenge_statements.find(1)) , :method => :get%>

    </div>

    <div class="challenge-red">
        <h1 class="second-title">#2 COMMENCEMENT CLASS GIVING 2021</h1>
        <div class="second-desc">
        <p>A key visual is not a logo design, but an effective add-on to the logo. It refers to an image motif used in campaigns in order to enhance brand recognition. The context of a campaign should be easily and quickly grasped from the key visual<span style="float:right">.</span></p>
        <p>The key visual should encapsulate a strong concept that is different from recent years and carry distinct elements that can be replicated in different formats. There is no need to use NUS colours or education and giving-related symbols/icons/motifs (e.g. heart, hands, gift box, plant, book, mortarboard, scroll, etc.)<span style="float:right">.</span></p>
        <p>Keep in mind that the Commencement Class Giving key visual will be adapted to suit different messaging and dimensions (e.g. web banners, emailers, lamp post banners, floor stickers, etc)<span style="float:right">.</span></p>
        <p>Commencement Class Giving is an annual tradition in which the graduating cohort of NUS comes together to celebrate convocation by making a single gift ($20.21 for Class of 2021) in support of their juniors. By leaving a legacy through their giving, the cohort contributes to current and future students in financial need, as well as activities that will enrich campus life<span style="float:right">.</span></p>
        </div>
        <br>

        <h1 class="second-title">COMPANY BACKGROUND</h1>
        <div class="second-desc">
        <p>The Development Office raises funds to support the development of the University<span style="float:right">.</span></p>
        <p>Annual Giving (AG) is a yearly campaign to alumni, staff, students, faculty and friends of the University to meet its financial needs, including University-wide bursaries and scholarships, as well as priority funds of different Faculties. It encourages donors to give mindfully and cultivate a habit of giving annually. The campaign runs from 1 April to 31 March the following year. Annual Giving oversees four different programmes: Commencement Class Giving, Faculty & Staff Giving, Alumni Giving, and Friends & Corporate Giving<span style="float:right">.</span></p>
        </div>
        <%= button_to 'Read More',  static_pages_challenge_statement_2_path(@challenge_statements.find(2)), :method => :get%>

    </div>

    <div class="challenge-orange">
        <h1 class="first-title padded-above-orange">#3 MASCOT FOR IT SECURITY AWARENESS CAMPAIGN</h1>
        <div class="first-desc">
        <p>This mascot character could be used as character on a website, an email, a poster, an intranet article, videos, and e-Learnings and so on to promote adopting good security habits. This mascot would potentially be converted to 3D format for live size representation.</p>
        <p>It should be possible to resize it depending on the action, so a high-quality graphics format is required. It should both work on a computer screen and on a printed poster.</p>
        <p>The target audience of mascot are students and staff of NUS.</p>
        </div>
        <br>

        <h1 class="first-title">COMPANY BACKGROUND</h1>
        <div class="first-desc padded-below-orange">
        <p>NUS Information Technology is the cornerstone for provision of reliable, high performance and secure IT infrastructure and effective IT governance and services for the campus.</p>
        </div>
        <%= button_to 'Read More',  static_pages_challenge_statement_3_path(@challenge_statements.find(3)), :method => :get%>
    </div>

    <div class="page-foot"><a href="#" class="last-link">ANY QUESTIONS?</a></div>
</div>
</body>
</html>